verbose_text: 10 The results from this study indicate that CP1, CP2 and F3.3.0 also reduced the synthesis of IL-2 (0.41, 0.6, and 0.74 ng/mL, respectively), whereas F3.3 did not significantly affect IL-2 synthesis (1.87 ng/mL) when compared with untreated cells (1.9 ng/mL).
